+++ b/_drafts/crack-down-phrasal-verb.md
@@ -0,0 +1,11 @@
+---
+id: crack-down-phrasal-verb
+title: Phrasal Verb: Crack Down On
+source: sources/videos/no-smoking-english-conversation-practice-episode-114
+status: draft
+created_at: 2026-05-13
+---
+
+- **一句話定義**："Crack down on" means to become stricter about stopping, limiting, or punishing a behavior.
+- **為什麼存在**：The phrase is common in news, law, school, workplace, and public-policy contexts. In the episode, smoking laws are "cracking down" by limiting where people can smoke. The same phrase can describe police cracking down on drunk driving, schools cracking down on lateness, or companies cracking down on policy violations.
+- **與既有概念的關聯**：Related to English idiom and phrase concepts like `up-to-code-phrase` because it helps learners understand rule and compliance language. It is not a duplicate because it focuses on enforcement becoming stricter.
diff --git a/_drafts/cut-down-vs-quit.md b/_drafts/cut-down-vs-quit.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..6add1d2224547f5673c87fbcf16ebf8749a657a2
--- /dev/null
+++ b/_drafts/cut-down-vs-quit.md
@@ -0,0 +1,11 @@
+---
+id: cut-down-vs-quit
+title: Cut Down vs Quit
+source: sources/videos/no-smoking-english-conversation-practice-episode-114
+status: draft
+created_at: 2026-05-13
+---
+
+- **一句話定義**："Cut down" means to reduce the amount or frequency of something, while "quit" means to stop doing it completely.
+- **為什麼存在**：The distinction prevents a common misunderstanding in habit-change conversations. Someone who says they will "cut down on smoking" is not promising zero cigarettes; they are promising fewer cigarettes. This pattern also transfers to food, workload, salt, alcohol, screen time, and other repeated behaviors.
+- **與既有概念的關聯**：Related to `expire-everyday-validity-verb` as another everyday verb pattern where the learner must understand practical usage rather than just dictionary meaning. It is also related to `smoking-cessation-vocabulary`, but deserves its own draft because the contrast is broadly reusable outside smoking.
